Package: nimix
Type: Package
Title: Bayesian Mixture Clustering and Regression with NIMBLE
Version: 1.3.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Achmad Syahrul", "Choir", email = "madsyair@stis.ac.id",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-7088-0646"))
Description: A 'nimble'-based framework for Bayesian mixture clustering and
    regression models (de Valpine dkk, 2017 <doi:10.1080/10618600.2016.1172487>).
    It supports diverse univariate and multivariate distributions across four
    inference paradigms: finite, infinite (Dirichlet process), spatial
    (Markov random field), and hidden-Markov mixtures. Features include
    tuned MCMC samplers and comprehensive post-processing tools for
    label-switching correction and cluster validation.
